Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{}. Once hot, add the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g}. Fry for ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @chipotle paste{20%g}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, mixed beans, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

Mash half of the beans in the frying pan with a #potato masher{}, bring to the boil, then lower to a simmer.

Cook until thickened slightly, ~{4-5%mins}, then remove from the heat.

In the meantime, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a #board{} and mash with a #fork{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

== Dressing and Guacamole ==

In a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @cider vinegar{15%ml} with the @sugar{½%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts).

Add the tomato and avocado to the #bowl{} of dressing.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

== Buns and Assembly ==

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} top down through the middle (but not all the way through). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%mins}.

Stir the @butter{20%g} into the veggie chilli.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little thick.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%g} in the dressing.

Transfer your buns to your plates, then spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the cut sides. Fill with your veggie chilli.

Sprinkle the cheese over the buns and spoon on the guacamole.

Serve with your salad alongside. Enjoy!